psalm.text:
[[Ps 33,2]]Give thanks to the LORD on the harp; 
with the ten stringed lyre chant his praises.
[[Ps 33,3]]Sing to him a new song; 
pluck the strings skillfully, with shouts of gladness.

[[Ps 33,4]]For upright is the word of the LORD, 
and all his works are trustworthy.
[[Ps 33,5]]He loves justice and right; 
of the kindness of the LORD the earth is full.

[[Ps 33,6]]By the word of the LORD the heavens were made; 
By the breath of his mouth all their host.
[[Ps 33,7]]He gathers the waters of the sea as in a flask; 
in cellars he confines the deep.

[[Ps 33,8]]Let all the earth fear the LORD; 
let all who dwell in the world revere him.
[[Ps 33,9]]For he spoke, and it was made; 
He commanded, and it stood forth.
